  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  respiratory failure

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe hypoxemia requiring an FiO2 &gt; 0.6

          -  Hemodynamic instability : defined as a variation of &gt; 20% in mean arterial pressure
             (MAP) and heart rate (HR) during the previous 2 hours; the need for high doses of
             catecholamines (namely &gt; 0.5 mcg/kg/min) and/or the need of major volume resuscitation
             (more than 2 liters of fluids in 2 hours)

          -  Impaired consciousness or absence of patient cooperation;

          -  Facial or laryngeal lesions contraindicating the use of NIV;

          -  Poor short term prognosis.

          -  Age &lt; 18 years old
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
